We have been through this whole argument over Thales's nationality before. It is universally agreed in the primary and secondary sources that Thales came from the Greek city of Miletus and that he spoke Greek. Although some sources claim that he was of Phoenician ancestry, there is no clear consensus on whether or not this was the case. I therefore think it is best to just leave his nationality out of the first sentence altogether, since it is seems to attract so much controversy.
